result.execSummary:
The defendant Jerry A. Schwister was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).
  • Manuf/Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

superMiscConds.notes: Court orders the fines, costs, and restitution in this file shall be paid from all funds received into the defendant's prison accounts in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement. If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant is not to obtain ANY prescription from ANY physician without the express authorization of the supervising agent and after the agent has discussed the situation the defendant faces with the treating physician.  Defendant is to sign all necessary releases. Defendant is to NEVER obtain a prescription from more than one physician unless and until he receives express authorization from the supervising agent.   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

records.addlTxt: 11:37 am cases called-14CF172, 15CF92 & 15CF130. Defendant Jerry A. Schwister in court with attorney John H. Wallace.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement for global resolution stated on record by DA Blader.  15CF92- Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: 15CF92-No Contest to Count 2 & Count 3-without repeater enhancers.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Count 1 & Count 4 & 15CF130. All matters now postured for sentencing. 14CF172-Revocation Order and Warrant received-no corrections or clarifications by either counsel. PSI discussed and defendant waives a PSI being conducted. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Attorney Wallace. Statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: 14CF172- 6 years Wisconsin State Prison System to be served as 3 years Initial Confinement & 3 years Extended Supervision. 136 days credit. Costs re-imposed as not previously paid-25% of inmate earnings. 15CF92- COUNT 2- 6 years Wisconsin State Prison to be served at 3 years Initial Confinement & 3 years Extended Supervision, concurrent to 14CF172. Credit for 136 days.  15CF92- Count 3-SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years, consecutive to 14CF172 & 15CF92-Count 2. CONDITIONS OF ES & Probation: Not to obtain ANY prescription from ANY physician without the express authorization of the supervising agent and after the agent has discussed the situation the defendant faces with the treating physician. Defendant is to sign all necessary releases. Defendant is NEVER to obtain a prescription from more than one physician unless and until express authorization from the agent. AODA and follow through. The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Terms of Agent. Costs ordered plus $320 buy reimbursement assessed. 25 % of inmate earnings. Court finds defendant eligible for CIP & SAP. DNA sample to be provided & surcharge. Appeal Rights Given.
